JOHANNESBURG – Bidvest Wits confirmed a host of player signings on Tuesday. The defending league champions who now find themselves scrapping for survival at the bottom of the Premiership log, secured the services of Edwin Gyimah, Robyn Johannes and Thobani Mncwango. Sifiso Myeni will also make a return to the club. “Bidvest Wits have confirmed the “precontract” signing of Thobani Mncwango, Robyn Johannes & Denis Weidlich with effect from 1 July 2018,” the club posted on twitter. “Edwin Gyimah has also signed with our club with effect from 1 January 2018. Sifiso Myeni has been recalled from his loan with immediate effect.”  African News Agency